Overview

KERNEL UNIT IS A TECHNOLOGY-DRIVEN COMPANY FOCUSED ON CREATING MODERN, HIGH-QUALITY DIGITAL SOLUTIONS. BORN FROM THE SHARED VISION OF THREE LONG-TIME FRIENDS, THE COMPANY COMBINES EXPERTISE IN COMPUTER SCIENCE, SOFTWARE ENGINEERING, AND COMPUTER ENGINEERING TO DELIVER SOFTWARE THAT IS EFFICIENT, SCALABLE, AND BUILT WITH PURPOSE.

OUR WORK REVOLVES AROUND INNOVATION, PRECISION, AND A DEEP UNDERSTANDING OF HOW TECHNOLOGY CAN SOLVE REAL PROBLEMS. WHETHER DEVELOPING APPLICATIONS, DESIGNING DIGITAL EXPERIENCES, OR EXPLORING NEW FIELDS WITHIN IT, OUR TEAM IS COMMITTED TO TRANSFORMING IDEAS INTO MEANINGFUL PRODUCTS.

WE BELIEVE IN CLEAN ARCHITECTURE, CONTINUOUS LEARNING, AND THE POWER OF COLLABORATION. EACH PROJECT IS APPROACHED WITH DEDICATION, ATTENTION TO DETAIL, AND THE DRIVE TO BUILD TECHNOLOGY THAT GENUINELY IMPROVES PEOPLE'S LIVES. AS A YOUNG BUT AMBITIOUS COMPANY, KERNEL UNIT CONTINUES TO GROW, EVOLVE, AND PUSH FORWARD, ALWAYS GUIDED BY OUR PASSION FOR THE DIGITAL WORLD AND OUR DESIRE TO SHAPE THE FUTURE THROUGH SOFTWARE.

Our Story

KERNEL UNIT WAS FOUNDED WITH A SIMPLE IDEA: TO BRING TOGETHER THREE COMPLEMENTARY FIELDS, COMPUTER SCIENCE, SOFTWARE ENGINEERING, AND COMPUTER ENGINEERING, INTO ONE UNIFIED SPACE FOR INNOVATION.

OUR JOURNEY BEGAN LONG BEFORE THE COMPANY EXISTED. AS CLOSE FRIENDS WHO SHARED THE SAME PASSION FOR TECHNOLOGY SINCE CHILDHOOD, WE ALWAYS EXCHANGED IDEAS, EXPLORED NEW CONCEPTS, AND LEARNED FROM ONE ANOTHER. OVER THE YEARS, THIS NATURAL CURIOSITY EVOLVED INTO SOMETHING GREATER: A DESIRE TO CREATE, BUILD, AND CONTRIBUTE TO THE TECHNOLOGICAL WORLD.

WHAT STARTED AS CASUAL CONVERSATIONS ABOUT NEW TRENDS, PROBLEM-SOLVING, AND PERSONAL PROJECTS EVENTUALLY GREW INTO A VISION, TO TRANSFORM OUR SHARED KNOWLEDGE INTO REAL SOLUTIONS. KERNEL UNIT WAS BORN FROM THIS CONNECTION: A TEAM BUILT ON TRUST, COLLABORATION, AND THE AMBITION TO DEVELOP HIGH-QUALITY DIGITAL PRODUCTS.

TODAY, OUR GOAL REMAINS THE SAME AS IN THE BEGINNING: TO CREATE A SPACE WHERE IDEAS CAN FLOURISH, WHERE CHALLENGES BECOME OPPORTUNITIES, AND WHERE TECHNOLOGY IS USED TO BUILD MEANINGFUL SOLUTIONS. WE VALUE OPEN COMMUNICATION, CONTINUOUS LEARNING, AND THE FREEDOM TO EXPLORE NEW PERSPECTIVES.

EVEN AS WE STEP INTO THE INDUSTRY PROFESSIONALLY, WE STAY TRUE TO OUR ROOTS. KERNEL UNIT IS MORE THAN A COMPANY, IT IS THE EVOLUTION OF A LIFELONG FRIENDSHIP DRIVEN BY CREATIVITY, PASSION, AND THE BELIEF THAT TOGETHER, WE CAN BUILD SOMETHING EXTRAORDINARY.

KERNEL
UNIT

KERNEL REPRESENTS THE CORE, THE ESSENTIAL PART OF ANY OPERATING SYSTEM, THE CENTRAL COMPONENT RESPONSIBLE FOR MANAGING PROCESSES, CONNECTING HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE, AND ENSURING THAT EVERYTHING FUNCTIONS HARMONIOUSLY. FOR US, IT SYMBOLIZES THE HEART OF TECHNOLOGY: PRECISION, STRUCTURE, AND THE INVISIBLE INTELLIGENCE THAT POWERS EVERYTHING BEHIND THE SCENES. CHOOSING "KERNEL" REFLECTS OUR COMMITMENT TO BUILDING SOLID FOUNDATIONS, WRITING CLEAN CODE, AND UNDERSTANDING THE INNER WORKINGS OF COMPLEX SYSTEMS. IT IS A REMINDER THAT GREAT SOLUTIONS START AT THE CORE.

UNIT REPRESENTS THE BOND, THE CONNECTION THAT TRANSFORMS INDIVIDUALS INTO SOMETHING GREATER THAN THE SUM OF THEIR PARTS. IT REFLECTS THE COLLABORATION, TRUST, AND SHARED PURPOSE THAT DEFINE OUR WORK AND GUIDE EVERY DECISION WE MAKE TOGETHER. FOR US, IT SYMBOLIZES UNITY, ALIGNMENT, AND THE STRENGTH THAT EMERGES WHEN DIFFERENT MINDS CONVERGE AROUND ONE VISION. CHOOSING "UNIT" REINFORCES OUR BELIEF IN TEAMWORK, IN BUILDING COLLECTIVELY, AND IN CREATING SOLUTIONS SHAPED BY SHARED EFFORT AND TRUE PARTNERSHIP.

Meet The Team

Juan Carlos Hidalgo Herrera

COMPUTER SCIENCE

I was born on December 12th, 2005, in So Paulo, Brazil, where I spent most of my childhood and adolescence. Growing up, I was always surrounded by creativity, curiosity, and a natural interest in understanding how things work. In 2020, I moved to Italy, a transition that was not easy, but one that brought me new opportunities and allowed me to continue my education in a completely different environment.

After completing my studies here, I was accepted into the University of Milan, where I began my journey in Computer Science. It was during this period that I truly connected with the world of technology. I discovered a passion for understanding systems, learning programming languages, and exploring how software can solve real problems and shape the future. Every semester has been an opportunity to dive deeper into the field, and I am continuously expanding my skills as I explore new areas within computer science.

I am currently pursuing a bachelor's degree in Science and Technology with a specialization in Computer Science, and I plan to continue my academic journey by pursuing a master's degree to further strengthen and expand my knowledge in the IT field. My goal is to prepare myself for a versatile career path, exploring areas such as software engineering, full-stack development, data analysis, and even AI development.

"Your future is created by the choices you make today."

Lucas Mantovani Boaro

COMPUTER ENGINEERING

I was born on December 14th, 2005, in So Paulo, Brazil, where I developed the inquisitive and curious nature that still defines me today. From an early age, I was driven by the desire to understand how things work and why systems behave the way they do. This mindset guided many of my decisions growing up and eventually led me to pursue Computer Engineering at the University of Campinas (Unicamp), where I have now completed my second year.

During my time at university, I actively sought opportunities to put theory into practice. I immersed myself in hackathons, developing smart contracts in Solidity for Ethereum-based projects and experimenting with automation systems using AI agents. I also joined CONPEC, the Junior Enterprise, where I worked in the commercial sector and learned how to translate technical ideas into real value by understanding client needs and expectations. These hands-on experiences allowed me to explore different paths within technology and understand the kind of impact I wanted to create.

Through this journey, I discovered that my true passion lies in the world of data. My goal is to combine my engineering background with my analytical mindset to build efficient data architectures, solve complex problems, and contribute to data-driven solutions that empower people and organizations.

"Fun fact: Juan once kicked a soccer ball so hard that he accidentally broke my arm. True story."

Felipe Alberto Santos

SOFTWARE ENGINEERING

I was born on February 14th, 2005, and grew up most of my life in Louveira, in the countryside of So Paulo, Brazil. It was there that I had the chance to meet incredible people like Juan and Lucas, friendships that helped shape who I am today and allowed me to grow not only as a professional, but also as a person. From a young age, I developed a natural curiosity for technology and how digital experiences influence the world around us.

I graduated in Software Engineering at FIAP, where I built a strong technical foundation and strengthened my passion for creating meaningful digital products. During this time, I joined the Apple Developer Academy, an experience that turned ideas into real applications. Developing iOS apps allowed me to combine creativity with engineering, using documentation, experimentation, and continuous self-learning to bring practical and valuable solutions to life.

Today, I work as a Mobile Software QA, applying critical thinking, attention to detail, and a strong sense of responsibility to ensure that products reach users with quality and purpose. I am constantly improving my skills and exploring new areas of mobile development, driven by the desire to build technology that truly matters and positively impacts people's lives.

"The difference between the crazy and the successful is consistency."
